1ï¸âƒ£ Character Classes (What to Match)

. â†’ Any char (except newline by default)

\d â†’ Digit (0-9)

\D â†’ Non-digit

\w â†’ Word char (a-z, A-Z, 0-9, _)

\W â†’ Non-word char

\s â†’ Whitespace (space, tab, \n, \r, \f)

\S â†’ Non-whitespace

Custom sets:

[abc] â†’ a, b, or c

[^abc] â†’ Not a, b, or c

[a-z] â†’ Any lowercase letter

[A-Z] â†’ Any uppercase letter

[0-9] â†’ Digit range

[a-zA-Z0-9._-] â†’ Allowed characters in emails/usernames

2ï¸âƒ£ Quantifiers (How Many)

* â†’ 0 or more

+ â†’ 1 or more

? â†’ 0 or 1

{n} â†’ Exactly n

{n,} â†’ n or more

{n,m} â†’ Between n and m

Examples:

\d+ â†’ one or more digits

[A-Z]{2,4} â†’ 2 to 4 uppercase letters

3ï¸âƒ£ Anchors & Boundaries

^ â†’ Start of string

$ â†’ End of string

\b â†’ Word boundary

\B â†’ Not a word boundary

Examples:

^Hello â†’ matches â€œHello worldâ€ but not â€œSay Helloâ€

\bcat\b â†’ matches â€œcatâ€ but not â€œcategoryâ€

4ï¸âƒ£ Groups & Alternation

(abc) â†’ Capturing group

